cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM 

This paper deals with the problem of estimating the 3D pose of object instances using convolutional neural networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes an end-to-end learning framework for directly regressing object poses, which involves the use of Siamese Networks. This suggests that the paper could also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) category. Additionally, the paper deals with robotics-related applications, which could place it in the cs.RO (Robotics) category. The paper also discusses the use of discriminative features, which could place it in the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) category. Finally, the paper deals with a novel hand-object dataset, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.MM (Multimedia) category.
